	<dt>mips: installations via SSH broken for Cobalt</dt>
	<dd>
	This was going to be a new feature for the release, but a bug was
	discovered at the last minute. A fixed image is available for
	<a href="http://people.debian.org/~tbm/cobalt/etch-beta2/nfsroot.tar.gz">download</a>.
	</dd>

	<dt>sparc: 2.4 netboot images need special parameter to boot</dt>
	<dd>
	The netboot image needs to be passed ramdisk_size=16000 to boot the 2.4
	kernel properly.
	</dd>

	<dt>sparc32: 2.6 kernel not supported</dt>
	<dd>
	Only the 2.4 kernel works with the sparc32 subarchitecture.
	</dd>
</dl>
